This paper deals with machine learning and statistics, specifically in finding a useful model for a subset of the population. The focus on linear regression and identifying a significant segment of the population suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely given the use of algorithms and theoretical analysis. cs.ST (Statistics) is relevant due to the statistical methods used in the paper. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is possible due to the algorithmic focus of the paper. Finally, cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possibility given the practical applications of the research.
